analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who signed an informed consent form (ICF).

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who were enrolled in the study.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: FA
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who were enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug. This set will be used for the primary and secondary efficacy analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled and received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the FA Set who have no major protocol deviations that would impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The list of major protocol deviations will be finalized prior to database lock. This set will be used for sensitivity analyses of the primary efficacy endpoint.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In FA Set with no major protocol deviations impacting the primary efficacy endpoint

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who received at least 1 dose of study drug. This set will be used for all safety analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient plasma concentration data to derive at least 1 PK parameter. This set will be used for all PK analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In Safety Set with sufficient plasma concentration data to derive at least 1 PK parameter

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.label: PD
analysisPopulations.description: All participants in the Safety Set who have sufficient PD data to derive at least 1 PD parameter. This set will be used for all PD analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: In Safety Set with sufficient PD data to derive at least 1 PD parameter

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age of the participant at baseline.

characteristics.name: Medical History
characteristics.description: Summary of medical history by system organ class (SOC) and preferred term (PT).

characteristics.name: Wilson Disease History
characteristics.description: A separate summary of Wilson Disease (WD) history will be provided.

characteristics.name: Prior Medications
characteristics.description: Summary of prior medications by Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) class and preferred term.

characteristics.name: Prior Medications for Wilson Disease
characteristics.description: A separate summary of prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease (WD).
